{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_on_s5_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Prevention"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"c53b76",
"children":[
"Prevention"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f49945",
"children":[
"The most important preventive measure for ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hepatocellular carcinoma",
"children":[
"HCC"
]
},
" is hepatitis B vaccination."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_on_s5_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Screening"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"db7551",
"children":[
"Screening"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"617ec4",
"children":[
"Guidelines recommend that all patients with cirrhosis be screened with abdominal ultrasonography every 6 months."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5c292d",
"children":[
"Serum ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"α-fetoprotein",
"children":[
"AFP"
]
},
" measurement alone is not recommended for HCC screening or surveillance."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_on_s5_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"535e0c",
"children":[
"Order contrast-enhanced CT or MRI of the liver when the abdominal ultrasound is abnormal. Because the advanced imaging findings of HCC are fairly characteristic (arterial phase enhancement), biopsy for confirmation is usually unnecessary."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_on_s5_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"073a1d",
"children":[
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Surgical resection or liver transplantation is first-line therapy."
]
},
" Patients with ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"Child-Turcotte-Pugh",
"children":[
"CTP"
]
},
" class A cirrhosis, without significant portal hypertension or jaundice, and with a singular lesion ≤5 cm should be considered for curative resection. Other patients should be considered for liver transplantation."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_on_s5_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_on_s5_5",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ac9578",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 60-year-old man with chronic hepatitis C and decompensated cirrhosis is found to have a 4-cm liver mass on screening ultrasonography. A CT scan showed the mass enhances on arterial phase."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"aa2ac2",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose hepatocellular carcinoma. For management, select liver transplantation."
]
}
]
}
]
},
